Accidental Release Prevention Program and Specific Prevention Steps

The Plant City Phosphate Complex is subject to the U.S. Occupation Safety and Health Administration's Process Safety Management (PSM) Standard, 29 CFR 1910.119.  As required by EPA, the PSM standard forms the basis for the Agency's RMP prevention program component.   The primary purpose of this facility's PSM Program is to safeguard our employees and nearby neighbors from exposure to ammonia by providing assistance in evaluating and updating the facility's process and mechanical safety procedures and programs. 

The objectives of the PSM Program are:

1.    To periodically review and update the facility's process/mechanical safety procedures and programs; 
2.    To provide for regular and periodic review of the facility's procedures to maintain compliance with OSHA's PSM regulations;
3. To perform Process Hazard Analyses on new and existing processes; and
4. To assure follow-up on the action items generated by the Process Hazard Analyses until completion.

